# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CURRENT: private access (LAN / Freebox WireGuard VPN).
# Plain HTTP is acceptable here because WireGuard already encrypts the transport.
# `header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}` makes Caddy set the REAL client IP
# authoritatively, so the app's rate-limiter can't be bypassed via a spoofed
# X-Forwarded-For header.
:80 {
  encode gzip zstd
  reverse_proxy app:3000 {
    header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}
    header_up X-Real-IP {remote_host}
  }
}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHEN GOING FULLY PUBLIC: comment out the :80 block above and uncomment this.
# Requires APP_HOST set to a real hostname (e.g. a free DuckDNS name) with a DNS
# record pointing at the box, plus forwarding ONLY 443 on the router. Caddy then
# auto-provisions a Let's Encrypt cert, redirects 80→443, and (with HSTS) forces
# HTTPS. Also set APP_BASE_URL=https://<host> in .env.production so the app
# marks its session + CSRF cookies Secure.
#
